{
  "note": "<div style=\"text-align:left\"><b>Is Equal? (NTM)</b> - checks if a string is made of two identical halves (e.g. <i>110110</i> = <i>110</i> + <i>110</i>), without any separator.<br><br>\n<b>How it works:</b> Because there is no <i>#</i> marking the middle, the machine non-deterministically <i>guesses</i> the midpoint. It marks off matching characters from both halves and accepts if everything cancels out perfectly.<br><br>\n<b>States:</b>\n<ul>\n  <li><b>S0</b>  : The guessing state. Non-deterministically either: marks the current character (0→A, 1→B) and moves right to keep scanning, <i>or</i> decides the midpoint has been reached and moves left to S1. On a blank, goes to S7.</li>\n  <li><b>S1</b>  : Rewinds left over any already-marked characters (A, B) back to the start of the tape. When it hits a blank (left edge), moves to S2.</li>\n  <li><b>S2</b>  : Scans right, skipping already-crossed characters (X). When it finds an <i>A</i>, crosses it out and moves to S3. When it finds a <i>B</i>, crosses it out and moves to S4. If it hits a blank, all characters matched , moves to S6.</li>\n  <li><b>S3</b>  : Looks for a matching <i>0</i> in the right half. Skips over A, B, X. When it finds <i>0</i>, crosses it out and moves left to S5.</li>\n  <li><b>S4</b>  : Looks for a matching <i>1</i> in the right half. Skips over A, B, X. When it finds <i>1</i>, crosses it out and moves left to S5.</li>\n  <li><b>S5</b>  : Rewinds left past all remaining characters (A, B, 0, 1, X) back to the left boundary, then moves to S2 for the next round.</li>\n  <li><b>S6</b>  : Accept. All characters matched perfectly.</li>\n  <li><b>S7</b>  : Handles the empty string edge case , immediately accepts via S6.</li>\n</ul></div>",
